    @Override
    public void onBindViewHolder(@NonNull RecyclerView.ViewHolder holder, int position) {
        Item item = items.get(position);
        
        /* Cast first */
        ViewHolder viewHolder = (ViewHolder) holder;

        /* Then use */
        viewHolder.textView8.setText(item.getTextView8());
        viewHolder.textView7.setText(item.getTextView7());
        viewHolder.textView10.setText(item.getTextView10());
    }

Your ViewHolder type is ```ViewHolder``` (you could change your class name to something more appropriate), whilst the function override provides the type you extend, which is ```RecyclerView.ViewHolder```.

